  <entry>
    <title>8.0.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@8.0.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@8.0.0</id>
    <updated>2026-04-14T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      <strong>Breaking:</strong> <code>cell.css</code> <code>--monospace-font-family</code> no longer prefers <cite>DejaVu Sans Mono</cite> (TTF webfonts are unreliable in Safari); it now matches <cite>libertine.css</cite> with <code>Menlo, Consolas, monospace</code>.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>7.2.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@7.2.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@7.2.0</id>
    <updated>2026-04-13T12:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      Non-breaking minor release.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>7.1.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@7.1.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@7.1.0</id>
    <updated>2026-04-13T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      <code>cell.css</code>: braille loading animation for cells in the pending (<code>observablehq--running</code>) state. Documentation adds a <code>cell.css</code> section with pending and rejected state examples.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>7.0.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@7.0.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@7.0.0</id>
    <updated>2026-02-28T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      <strong>Breaking changes</strong> to Observable notebook imports: the runtime now initializes with Observable stdlib builtins (for names like <code>DOM</code> and <code>width</code>), and includes a <code>runtime.fileAttachments</code> compatibility extension for transitive notebook imports.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>6.0.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@6.0.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@6.0.0</id>
    <updated>2025-07-29T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      <code>data-observe</code> is now <code>data-display</code>.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>5.0.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@5.0.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@5.0.0</id>
    <updated>2025-07-29T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      <code>celine.cell(name, ...)</code> now renders above <code>data-observe=name</code>, not <code>id=name</code>.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>4.0.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@4.0.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@4.0.0</id>
    <updated>2024-12-11T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      <code>cell.css</code> now uses a light theme.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>3.0.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@3.0.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@3.0.0</id>
    <updated>2024-11-19T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      <code>cell.css</code> has been moved to be a top-level export from <code>@celine/celine</code>. Check the Installation section to see how to include the stylesheet in your project.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>2.0.0</title>
    <link href="https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@2.0.0"/>
    <id>https://jsr.io/@celine/celine@2.0.0</id>
    <updated>2024-11-19T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[
      The <code>libertine.css</code> stylesheet has been split off into its own package (<code>@celine/libertine</code>) so that stylistic changes are not breaking changes to <code>@celine/celine</code>. This is a breaking change because <code>libertine.css</code> is no longer included in the <code>@celine/celine</code> package. Check the Installation section to see how to include the stylesheet in your project.
    ]]></summary>
  </entry>

